  "descriptions": [
    {
      "descrType": "Overview",
      "description": "The 9M96DM is an extended-range variant and improved development of the 9M96 medium-range air defense missile, specifically integrated with the S-400 Triumf system. Introduced in the mid-2000s, the 9M96DM extends the effective engagement envelope to 150 kilometers while maintaining the compact form factor that enables quad-packing in a single launch tube. The missile enhances high-altitude interception capability and provides improved guidance through advanced active radar homing. Like its predecessor, the 9M96DM employs gas-dynamic thrust-vector control for high-maneuverability terminal-phase engagement.",
      "shortDescription": "Extended-range variant of the 9M96 with improved high-altitude capability and enhanced guidance.",
      "classification": "U"
    },
    {
      "descrType": "Design",
      "description": "The 9M96DM retains the compact airframe architecture of the baseline 9M96 but incorporates performance enhancements through improved propulsion and guidance algorithms. The solid-fuel rocket motor is optimized for extended-range cruise while maintaining subsonic and transonic flight profiles to reduce energy signature and extend endurance. Enhanced active radar homing guidance provides improved track stability and terminal-phase accuracy. The gas-dynamic control system, employing lateral thrusters, delivers exceptional maneuverability for engagement of targets executing evasive maneuvers. The warhead remains a pre-fragmented anti-aircraft type, optimized for aerial threats. Quad-packing capability is maintained, allowing four 9M96DM missiles to occupy a single launch tube on the S-400 TEL.",
      "shortDescription": "Improved compact SAM with extended range, active radar homing, and thrust-vector control.",
      "classification": "U"
    }
  ],
